  <title>CIFAL : Sustainable agriculture &amp; climate change adaptations</title>
  <description>The project aims to improve sustainable food security and livelihoods of vulnerable communities through capacity building programmes and effective climate change strategies and interventions. The project will increase the knowledge and skills of 140 community leaders in Kulna and Bagerhat to engage in climate change mitigation. The communities will be trained in techniques to increase food and water production and will be given assistance to build climate change adapted houses. The project will also seek to influence policy reform at local, regional, national and international levels.</description>
